<title>UK: Ex-dividends take 2.877 points off UK's FTSE index.</title>
<headline>Ex-dividends take 2.877 points off UK's FTSE index.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>FTSE International said the following FTSE 100 stocks go ex-dividend on Tuesday and the effect would be to take 2.877 points off the index in early trading.</p>
<p>					     DIVIDEND	INDEX</p>
<p>					     (PENCE)	 EFFECT</p>
<p>	COMPANY			  Net   Gross    Gross</p>
<p> * Blue Circle Industries	  9.00   11.25    0.486</p>
<p> * Guinness			   11.55   14.44    1.591</p>
<p> * Kingfisher			 14.00   17.50    0.687</p>
<p> * Lasmo (Ordinary)		  1.60    2.00    0.113</p>
<p>(a) The dividend for Lasmo is a Foreign Income Dividend (FID) of 2p gross.</p>
<p>-- London Newsroom +44 171 542 7954</p>
